<p>I've looked into several ways to do this and none seem to work for me.</p>  <p>I have the following xml example:</p>  <pre><code> &lt;Entry&gt;       &lt;Node1&gt;&lt;/Node1&gt;       &lt;Node2&gt;&lt;/Node2&gt;       &lt;Node3&gt;&lt;/Node3&gt;  &lt;/entry&gt; </code></pre>  <p>I need the xsd to account for the following changes without breaking:</p>  <p>1) New node added to the end of the xml:</p>  <pre><code> &lt;Entry&gt;       &lt;Node1&gt;&lt;/Node1&gt;       &lt;Node2&gt;&lt;/Node2&gt;       &lt;Node3&gt;&lt;/Node3&gt;       &lt;Node4&gt;&lt;/Node4&gt;  &lt;/Entry&gt; </code></pre>  <p>2) New node added in the middle of the xml:</p>  <pre><code> &lt;Entry&gt;       &lt;Node1&gt;&lt;/Node1&gt;       &lt;Node4&gt;&lt;/Node4&gt;       &lt;Node2&gt;&lt;/Node2&gt;       &lt;Node3&gt;&lt;/Node3&gt;  &lt;/Entry&gt; </code></pre>  <p>3) Combination of both:</p>  <pre><code> &lt;Entry&gt;       &lt;Node1&gt;&lt;/Node1&gt;       &lt;Node2&gt;&lt;/Node2&gt;       &lt;Node5&gt;&lt;/Node5&gt;       &lt;Node3&gt;&lt;/Node3&gt;       &lt;Node4&gt;&lt;/Node4&gt;  &lt;/Entry&gt; </code></pre>  <p>The XSD I'm currently using is build off of <code>&lt;xs:sequence&gt;</code> and obviously that is failing. I've tried <code>&lt;xs:any&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;xs:all&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;xs:choice&gt;</code> and none of them seem to validate properly. </p>  <p>The use case for this is as follows: If a developer updates and API that returns the aforementioned XML I do not want to have to create a new XSD and recompile an application to allow for the changes. </p>  <p>Any and all information is greatly appreciated.</p>  <hr>  <p>Here is the xsd that I'm using for this. </p>  <pre><code>&lt;xs:schema attributeFormDefault="unqualified" elementFormDefault="qualified" xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema"&gt;   &lt;xs:element name="APIName"&gt;     &lt;xs:complexType&gt;       &lt;xs:sequence&gt;         &lt;xs:element name="entry" maxOccurs="unbounded" minOccurs="0"&gt;           &lt;xs:complexType&gt;               &lt;xs:element type="xs:string" name="Node1"/&gt;               &lt;xs:element type="xs:string" name="Node2"/&gt;               &lt;xs:element type="xs:string" name="Node3"/&gt;           &lt;/xs:complexType&gt;         &lt;/xs:element&gt;       &lt;/xs:sequence&gt;       &lt;xs:attribute type="xs:string" name="NextPageLink"/&gt;     &lt;/xs:complexType&gt;   &lt;/xs:element&gt; &lt;/xs:schema&gt; </code></pre>